The paper presents a study on deep learning architectures for predicting DNA- and RNA-binding specificities, which falls under the intersection of computer science and bioinformatics. The paper focuses on evaluating different deep learning architectures, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper deals with DNA and RNA sequences, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of quantitative methods in biology (q-bio.QM) and genomics (q-bio.GN).
